<p class="orange">RLUK and OCLC partner for shared collection management and visibility goals</p>

<p>November 14, 2014 &#151; &quot;OCLC and Research Libraries UK (RLUK), a consortium of the largest research organisations in the UK and Ireland, today announced an expanded partnership that will help RLUK achieve key strategic objectives for shared collection management and resource discovery.&quot;</p>

<p>&quot;Building on existing OCLC cataloguing arrangements, the new agreement offers RLUK members the opportunity to load their bibliographic metadata into <a href="http://www.oclc.org/worldcat.en.html">WorldCat</a>, the most comprehensive global network of data about library holdings and services. This data will then be used to facilitate better understanding and visibility of these resources for both RLUK as a group, and for individual members of the consortium....&quot;</p>

